{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777261072048,"sessionID":"ses_232ff08f4ffeIa4wbk7ukn1rV3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_bvM9OE7G18Y4OzmQ7aG7WO44","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"category":"quick","command":"analyze-mode context gathering","description":"Inspect task workflow patterns","load_skills":[],"prompt":"In D:\\agent_workspace, quickly inspect existing task-hall task directories or docs for patterns on engineering-leader publishing watched child tasks, linking parent-child tasks, and reporting. Do not modify files. Return concise commands/patterns and any gotchas.","run_in_background":false,"session_id":"","subagent_type":""},"output":"SUPERVISED TASK COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY\n\nIMPORTANT: This model (MoreCode/gemini-3-flash) is marked as unstable/experimental.\nYour run_in_background=false was automatically converted to background mode for reliability monitoring.\n\nDuration: 2m 47s\nAgent: Sisyphus-Junior (category: quick)\n\nMONITORING INSTRUCTIONS:\n- The task was monitored and completed successfully\n- If you observe this agent behaving erratically in future calls, actively monitor its progress\n- Use background_cancel(task_id=\"...\") to abort if the agent seems stuck or producing garbage output\n- Do NOT retry automatically if you see this message - the task already succeeded\n\n---\n\nRESULT:\n\nBased on the inspection of the `task-hall` system in `D:\\agent_workspace`, here are the patterns for engineering-leader task publishing, linking, and reporting.\n\n### Core Patterns & Commands\n\n#### 1. Publishing Watched Child Tasks\nThe **Engineering Leader** delegates work to \"builders\" by publishing tasks in **watched** mode. This creates a callback loop where the leader is notified of progress.\n\n*   **Pattern**: `mycli task-hall publish-raw <file> <category> <priority> <tags> watched <publisher-agent> <session-id> <agent-type>`\n*   **Key Command**:\n    ```powershell\n    mycli task-hall publish-raw ./task.md custom high \"engineering,build\" watched opencode/engineering-leader ses_123 middle-builder\n    ```\n*   **Metadata (`meta.json`)**:\n    *   `publish_mode: \"watched\"`: Signals the system to track handoffs and callbacks.\n    *   `required_agent_type`: Restricts execution to specific pools (e.g., `middle-builder`, `senior-builder`).\n\n#### 2. Linking Parent-Child Tasks\nRelationships are managed via the `task-link` subsystem and stored in JSON sidecars under `state/task-links/`.\n\n*   **Explicit Linking**: `mycli task-hall link <parent_id> <child_id>`\n*   **Relationship Management**:\n    *   `mycli task-hall task-link show <task_id>`: Shows the full state of a linked/watched task.\n    *   `mycli task-hall task-link switch-agent <task_id> <new_agent>`: Hand off a child task to a different executor.\n\n#### 3. Reporting & Callbacks\nThe reporting loop ensures the Leader stays in control without micro-managing.\n\n*   **Executor Reporting**: `mycli task-hall task-link report <task_id> <report_file> [status]`\n*   **Notification Dispatch**:\n    *   `mycli task-hall dispatch-callbacks`: Routes \"reported\" events back to the `publisher_agent` session.\n    *   `mycli task-hall callback-queue`: Monitors pending notifications for the leader.\n\n### Key Monitoring Files\n*   `capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\task-links\\*.json`: Source of truth for watched task status and callback history.\n*   `capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\monitor\\lifecycle-state.json`: Global view of all agents and their currently claimed tasks.\n\n### Critical Gotchas\n*   **Callback Failures**: If `publisher_agent` is not a valid agent ID recognized by `dispatch-callbacks`, the reporting loop will break and the status will hang in `waiting_publisher`.\n*   **Sidecar Logic**: While `meta.json` in the task directory has `parent_id` and `child_ids` fields, the active \"Watched\" logic primarily relies on the separate JSON files in `state/task-links/`.\n*   **Reporting Protocol**: Executors should write reports to markdown files named `task-link-report-<timestamp>.md` to follow the standard inspection pattern used by the leader.\n\n<task_metadata>\nsession_id: ses_232febfa7ffeE3QYy9FVSpNexV\n</task_metadata>\n\nto continue: task(session_id=\"ses_232febfa7ffeE3QYy9FVSpNexV\", load_skills=[], run_in_background=false, prompt=\"...\")","metadata":{"truncated":false,"prompt":"In D:\\agent_workspace, quickly inspect existing task-hall task directories or docs for patterns on engineering-leader publishing watched child tasks, linking parent-child tasks, and reporting. Do not modify files. Return concise commands/patterns and any gotchas.","agent":"Sisyphus-Junior","category":"quick","load_skills":[],"description":"Inspect task workflow patterns","run_in_background":false,"sessionId":"ses_232febfa7ffeE3QYy9FVSpNexV","command":"analyze-mode context gathering","model":{"providerID":"MoreCode","modelID":"gemini-3-flash"}},"title":"Inspect task workflow patterns","time":{"start":1777260904513,"end":1777261072044}},"id":"prt_dcd013ecf0013aIovT9hwJp2qj","sessionID":"ses_232ff08f4ffeIa4wbk7ukn1rV3","messageID":"msg_dcd01221f001Dyi29b1JWsOZJy"}}
